message.body: Hey what's going on
Hey!
I think it finally worked!
Good thing
How much time do you have to text?
I'm free til I leave for class (which is like 4:30) so whenever is good
Ok let's chat till then
What class do you have today
I have my science methods class
It's basically teaching us how to teach science
But my prof is crazy and I get so annoyed every time I'm in class lol
Is it finals time?
Is that why its stressful
Next week is the last week of class but I mostly have papers and stuff due
So no exams or anything, just long papers
What about you? What have you been up to?
What's the issue with this teacher
He just makes stuff up and I know it can't be true
Gardening and starting to ride my bike a bit.
I'm just the kind of person when I hear his exaggerated stories I can't trust him as a teacher
That sounds like bad teaching
Yeah, I'm so over his class. Thankfully it's almost over!
What have you been gardening? Do you do like fruits and veggies and stuff?
It's amazing there are bad teachers out there with all the people looking for teaching jobs
We have a fig tree
I planted lots of herbs and radishes carrots and cucumbers fennel and greens
Oh cool! It's so hard to find planting space in the city
Do u have plans after the semester is over
The house I live in has a small back yard
I'm taking a short online class this summer
But other than that, I'll probs spend my time reading/writing and playing frisbee.
Do you have any plans for the summer?
Not yet but I am going to a wedding this weekend
Prob just go to the shore a few times
Ooh fun! Weddings are always so much fun.
It should be fun, a lot of old friends will be there.
Yeah, it's always so nice to see people again esp if you haven't seen them in a while
Yes, it seems like a lot of friends have moved away in the last few years
Do u play frisbee on a team? How seriously do you take it?
It brings everyone together
So what other hobbies do you like to do?
Yeah, I'm involved in the frisbee community here
I make paintings and sculpture sometimes
I play pretty much year round (indoors in the winter)
Is it frisbee golf?
And I play "club" which is the level after college
And we're pretty serious, lol. We've flown all over the place to play in tournaments, though I think my favorite was San Deigo bc the weather was so nice that
I didn't want to leave
That is awesome!
Is there a pro level?
Nope, that's different, though I've played that too
Ultimate frisbee is kinda like football
You have to score in an endzone
And you can't run with the frisbee so every time you catch it, you have a pivot foot and have to throw it to advance it up the field
They just started pro last yr!
That sounds really fun. Is it full contact like American football?
I like soccer but don't play on any teams
It's actually semi-pro, but they call it pro
And it hasn't caught on everywhere yet unlike the club level which is pretty much everywhere
Philly actually has two pro teams in the two pro leagues
What kind of paintings and sculptures do you do?
That is crazy, you could go pro!
There's a "no contact" rule
And Philly has a huge Ultimate community so we're really lucky here
A lot of our players are converts from soccer bc there's so much running and they see the field in the same way
I paint oils and water colors and do mostly found object sculpture
So contact is usually a foul
And everything is call your own fouls so ppl can't get away with it!
It is really fun! I've been addicted to it since high school, lol.
I feel like there is a bit of a delay. I'm getting your texts after I have responded to them. It is slightly out of sync
That's cool do you like soccer too?
I like going to watch the Union play when I can.
Yeah there's def a delay and it's not always consistent. It's like a fluctuating delay or something
I've never played soccer or anything
I've heard fun things about the Union but I've never been
The only pro soccer game I've seen was when I was studying abroad in Germany
And that game was awesome
I played soccer since I was 5. It's the sport I understand intuitively the best.
Union games are really fun.
I'm going to one on the 5th.
Definitely not as intense as the European clubs though
Soccer is very spatial, I think, with all the angles and such
Germany must have been crazy. I would have seen when I was there.
Haha yeah, my friend has season tix and was saying how fun they are
Yes, the field is so big that you really need to strategize where to position yourself.
Yeah it was super intense! Like much more than I expected
We were all freezing and huddled up, but everyone was just going crazy
The atmosphere was awesome
Soccer has a bit of chess in it.
Yeah, I def like that about the game, that you have to predict where ppl are gonna go
It gets rowdy at Union games but not scary rowdy like in much of the world.
I used to play indoor soccer too. It was like speed chess, is indoor frisbee like that as well?
That's true, though I feel like Philly is especially prone to riots (like celebratory riots) lol
Yeah! It's called "sprint format" and the rules are slightly different and much faster paced
It's actually my favorite (despite all the running)
Yes I used to like indoor soccer more because you could use the walls like another player and the games we generally higher scoring.
The Union is doing pretty good this year. I hope I get to see a victory when I go on the 5th
Oh that's cool! In indoor frisbee the walls/nets are out of bounds so if it touches, the other team gets it at that point
That's cool that they're doing well! I'm all for Philly sports to try to bring home some trophies
Indoor soccer has a hockey element to it so you can play the ball off the walls but above the walls is a net
The net is out of bounds and if you hit it I
The ball goes to the other team
The Union is not the best team this year just doing well. Last year they weren't so great.
They have a new young forward who has the most goals in the league this year.
That's awesome!
Is there a minor league for soccer? Where does the league get new recruits?
There is minor league teams I think but most players come out of college or from Europe.
A lot of the older stars in Europe play here when they can't hang in Europe anymore.
It's great to have veteran players on the team to teach the younger players
Oh that makes sense
Do you think those European players help pull people to games in the US?
Like to watch
And it's really cool for the American fans to see these European stars play.
Yes for sure
Like Beckham did for LA
Yeah that was awesome
Did you play sports as a kid?
I guess ppl who are in to soccer will know all the European names too
Did Beckham leave LA? Is he back in Britain?
He plays in France now I think. But he is way old
I played softball and field hockey and then when I got to hs I played golf for a yr then started playing Ultimate
You stayed active!
Do you do anything other than frisbee with your free time
Lol yeah, I kept busy
I play bass guitar and I read a lot. I write too.
Do you play in a band
Free time is so sparse lol
I did in hs but most of my friends who play have moved away. I play in my church band but it's not quite the same
I can imagine
I guess I watch TV too. Have you watched any good shows lately?
Have u seen any good films lately
I really like the British show Peep Show
But it's not new
What's that about?
I've been watching a bunch of British shows lately like Doctor Who and Misfits
Two roommates in London who are both awful human beings in very different ways
Lol that sounds very British
I watched a little dr who, what is the misfits?
Also I
Watch the Inbetweeners
It's about British school mates
Misfits is about a group of young people who have community service but then get struck by a storm and develop super powers
Black Books is a show I used to like when I lived in the uk
And craziness ensues
I've heard about the Inbetweeners. I think they made it into an American show too?
What's that Black Books about?
Like x men
How much longer can u txt for?
Til 4:30 then I'll be heading out
Black books is about an alcoholic that owns a book shop and is horrible at running a business.
It's a comedy!
But it seems like it's delaying a lot
Ok send me a txt when you need to stop
I've never seen the american Inbetweeners
Ok
Is Black Books still on? I've been trying to find more BBC shows to watch on Netflix
I do like That Mitchell And Web Look as well.
Black books is on Hulu I think
Have you seen The IT Crowd?
Also Snuff Box is a great British comedy too
That's a British comedy which is super funny
I'm going to have to check all these out!
I just finished watching Veronica Mars so I need something else to watch
I think I did once. The IT Crowd has some of the same actors as Snuff Box
Ok check them out and we can txt about them next time!
Oh awesome! I really liked those actors!
I saw a couple episodes of VM but never got into it.
Have you seen the British Sherlock?
Do you like the show Louie?
No but I have heard good things about Sherlock
I saw the first season of Louie but the second season got too dark for me.
His stand up is hilarious tho!
Yeah it can be depressing
Oh man, Sherlock is one of my faves (along with Misfits)
I'll have to give them a try.
Def check is out!! The guy who plays Sherlock is awesome (and is going to be in the new Star Trek movie)
But Sherlock is 90 mins each so you kind of have to commit but the seasons are only three eps (and there's only two seasons)
Woah, there is guna be a new Star Trek movie?!
Yeah!! I'm super excited! The trailer looks awesome
I'm guna look it up
Alright I'm heading out. Did you want to text tomorrow? I don't even know what time we'd be able to since today was all quirky
I'm txt with another participant tomorrow so probably Monday is my next available time. Email me to coordinate . See ya
See ya!
